### English Title:
US Military Conducts Airstrikes on Yemeni Port to Cut Off Houthi Revenues

### English Text Summary:
The US military announced airstrikes on the Ras Issa port in Yemen's Al Hudaydah province, aimed at disrupting revenue streams for the Houthi group. The Central Command stated that the port has been generating illegal profits for the Houthis since their designation as a foreign terrorist organization in April. The strikes are intended to weaken the economic power of the militants without harming civilians. The Houthis, who control much of northern Yemen, claimed that the airstrikes resulted in at least 20 deaths and 50 injuries, primarily among workers and paramedics. The article also notes the ongoing international efforts to disrupt Houthi arms smuggling and their attacks on commercial vessels in the Red Sea.

